# Environment Configuration for BugBox Features

# Backend Environment Variables (.env)

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/bugbox

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key_here
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# Email Service (Gmail recommended)
EMAIL_SERVICE=gmail
EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-app-specific-password

# Frontend URL
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# OpenAI API (for AI bug analysis)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key

# AWS S3 (for cloud video storage)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_S3_BUCKET=your-s3-bucket-name

# Server
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Gmail Configuration
- Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
- Create an app-specific password
- Use this password in EMAIL_PASSWORD (not your main Gmail password)

### 2. OpenAI Configuration
- Get API key from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
- Paste in OPENAI_API_KEY

### 3. AWS S3 Configuration
- Create an S3 bucket in AWS Console
- Create an IAM user with S3 access
- Get access key and secret key
- Configure bucket CORS policy:
```json
[
  {
    "AllowedHeaders": ["*"],
    "AllowedMethods": ["GET", "PUT", "POST"],
    "AllowedOrigins": ["http://localhost:5173", "http://localhost:3000"],
    "ExposeHeaders": [],
    "MaxAgeSeconds": 3000
  }
]
```

### 4. MongoDB
- Install MongoDB locally or use MongoDB Atlas
- Update MONGODB_URI accordingly

---

## Features Configuration

### AI-Based Bug Detection
- Automatically analyzes bug titles and descriptions
- Detects severity (Critical, High, Medium, Low)
- Categorizes bugs (UI, Performance, Logic, Security, Database, API)
- Finds duplicate/related bugs
- Provides fix suggestions

### Automatic Log Collection
- Console logs (all levels)
- Network requests (fetch/API calls)
- User interactions (clicks, inputs, scrolls)
- Performance metrics (memory, load time)
- Browser and OS information

### Cloud Video Storage (AWS S3)
- Automatic upload of screen recordings to S3
- Generates public, shareable URLs
- Falls back to local storage if S3 not configured
- Automatic cleanup of old files

### Notification System
- Real-time notifications via Socket.IO
- Email notifications (configurable)
- Notification types:
  - New bug reports
  - Status changes
  - New comments
  - Critical severity alerts
- Unread notification tracking
- Mark as read functionality
